I have added a new part to my ending statement.I now recommend that all the guitars I sell be set up to your preferences. ALL GUITARS MAY REQUIRE SET UP!!! Players have such varied opinions that I no longer want to hear about it. Here is a very cool Squier "Custom Shack Strat". The Squier maple neck has zero fret wear,and has had a nice headstock make over with many coats of cleat over the decal. I upgraded the closed back tuners with some nice vintage looking Kluson styyle tuners. The very cool Gloss Seafoam Green Body looks very nice, only the mildest of surface scratches. The pickups have been upgraded with some nice hot ceramic single coils,8k-neck,9k-middle,10k-bridge ,and the guitar has been wired for tone control on all three pickups.The bridge and neck pickups both work with the neck pickups tone control. Nice to have tone control on the bridge pickup,makes it a lot more versatile. All electronics work perfectly,and sound great on every setting,clean or with some distortion. The capacitor has been upgraded with a .033uf axial capacitor . More range of tone control and a smoother response. I added the brown tortoise pickguard,rear tremolo cover,cream pickup covers,switch tip and whammy bar tip to get the vibe I was going for. This guitar sounds really good,and it looks super cool. Plays smooth with low action,sounds great, and looks very cool. This "Custom Shack" came out great!!! A very sexy looking guitar,great colors.
